Tue Jul 28 04:01:40 1998  pavlov

	* TODO, INSTALL, README:
	Update of the documentation (or sad excuse for that).  Added the INSTALL file
	to replace the one thats automagically generated if it doesn't exist.  This
	way we get a file that accually applies to the installation of balsa, and not
	generic stuff.  This should help, not that its hard to do now that c-client is
	removed.

	Updated the TODO file to note that local mailbox dir recursion now is
	implimented but lacks a way to store the mailboxes in something other than a
	list currently.  This will be GForest's use.

	Updated README to remove INSTALL file info, and such.  Added a description,
	etc.

	* src/balsa-app.c, libbalsa/mailbox.c, libbalsa/Attic/gforrest.c, libbalsa/gforest.c, libbalsa/gforest.h, libbalsa/Makefile.am:
	whoops, i really need a dictionary...  gnome dictionary interface?  hehe... :)

	thanks to Tom Tromey for pointing out that forest is spelled with one r and
	not two :)

	a few minor cleanups, make a little bit more use of some g_get_* functions.

	Stuart Parmenter <pavlov@pavlov.net>

	* libbalsa/Attic/gforrest.c, libbalsa/gforrest.h:
	whoops, I forgot to add gforrest.[ch].

	This currently doesn't do anything useful, but will be used to store things in
	a heirarchy.  Since GTree is already being used, i figured we'd just use
	forrest (;

	Once it does something useful, we'll probibly add it to glib.  If someone
	wants to do this for me, or already has, please speak up :)

	Stuart Parmenter <pavlov@pavlov.net>

	* libbalsa/send.h, libbalsa/send.c, libbalsa/misc.h, libbalsa/misc.c, libbalsa/Attic/mbox.c, libbalsa/mailbox.h, libbalsa/mailbox.c, libbalsa/libbalsa.c, libbalsa/Attic/drivers.h, libbalsa/Makefile.am:
	changed the licence of libbalsa back to GPL.
	Removed some excess files from libbalsa that were no longer used.

	* src/local-mailbox.c, src/balsa-init.c:
	Fixed local-mailbox.c so that it loads mailboxes recursivly in your local mail
	dir.

	Fixed balsa-init.c so that it doesn't do a few weird things.

	-pav

