	doing it.  *shrug*
	-pav

	* TODO: updated TODO list
	-pav

	* src/balsa-message.c:
	oops, left in debugging stuff that made your screen a mess.
	-pav

	* src/balsa-message.c:
	ok, fixed spacing issues so that we don't replace every space with a &nbsp;
	because if we did, it produced non-wrapping lines.

	I've got it checking to see if there are 3 spaces in a row, and replacing them
	with "&nbsp; &nbsp;" and else if there are 2 spaces in a row, "&nbsp; "  I
	think this should address all problems there may be.  Let me know if you can
	think of a situation this wouldn't account for.  ok, thanks. bye :)

	-pav

	* src/balsa-message.c: more changes.. *yawn*
	-pav

	* src/balsa-message.c:
	more changes (almost fixed spacing issues.. xmhtml does stupid stuff though,
	so i need to have a little talk with miguel :))

	-pav

	* src/sendmsg-window.c, src/pref-manager.c, src/main-window.c, src/Attic/c-client.h, src/Attic/c-client.c, src/balsa-message.c, src/balsa-index.c, src/balsa-app.h, src/balsa-app.c:
	wow, lots of changes i guess

	c-client.c now has a get_header(char *, ...) function which lets you grab a
	header from whatever you told it..  it returns "" if the header doesn't exist.

	balsa-message.c doesn't use <pre></pre> anymore.  instead, i've got it
	converting all \r\n's into <br>, \r's into <br>, and \n's into <br>s  This
	allows for word wrapping!  Much nicer than scrolling over and over and over..
	thats kinda dumb don'tcha think?

	pre-manager.c was updated to support everything that it should have in it.  it
	doesn't update the config files yet, but thats kinda easy to do.

	balsa-app.c was updated to load mbx formated mailboxes from ~/Mail/* on load.
	I'm not yet overly sold on this format, since it seems to be a little faster,
	but more cpu and memory intensive.

	balsa-app.h was updated to make the pre-manager width a little wider

	sendmsg-window was updated to support the new get_header() function

	balsa-index.c wasn't updated that i remember, except mabey for me widening the
	message number column.

	-pav

