Fri Apr 10 13:33:37 1998  pavlov

	* src/balsa-app.c:
	used mail_valid instead of mail_open to check for validation of the mailbox so
	it doesn't have to load the entire mailbox to check its format... seems to
	make it much faster :)

	-pav

	* src/Attic/c-client.c, src/balsa-app.c:
	some misc changes... balsa-app now loads the mailboxes in ~/.gnome/balsa
	specified in the mailbox directory thingy somewhat properly.  right now it
	opens the mailbox before adding it to check the mailbox format, which is slow
	as hell as is, and should probibly be done some other way, but it was just a
	quick hack.  i made mm_exists check to make sure the main_window is created
	since that callback seems to be called before the main window is initialized.
	i didn't touch addrbook-manager.c that i know of, but what the hell.
	-pav

